{
  "_protected": {
    "comment": [
      "── HARNESS-ENGINEERING PROTECTED CONFIG ──",
      "DO NOT RELAX THESE FLAGS. They encode the testing-pyramid types contract",
      "from docs/standard/v0.1.md §2.5 and carry forward the lessons from:",
      "  - retro 014 (noPropertyAccessFromIndexSignature — bracket-access env vars)",
      "  - retro 015 (Python strict typing parity)",
      "Relaxing a strict flag here means a strictly weaker type guarantee than",
      "declared in the slot decision docs. If a flag must change, file a",
      "hypothesis-first experiment per CLAUDE.md.",
      "JSON does not support comments natively; the `_protected` key carries",
      "the sentinel. Tooling ignores unknown keys.",
      "──────────────────────────────────────────"
    ]
  },
  "compilerOptions": {
    "target": "ES2022",
    "module": "ESNext",
    "moduleResolution": "Bundler",
    "lib": ["ES2022", "DOM", "DOM.Iterable"],
    "strict": true,
    "noUncheckedIndexedAccess": true,
    "noImplicitOverride": true,
    "exactOptionalPropertyTypes": true,
    "noImplicitReturns": true,
    "noFallthroughCasesInSwitch": true,
    "noPropertyAccessFromIndexSignature": true,
    "esModuleInterop": true,
    "skipLibCheck": true,
    "resolveJsonModule": true,
    "isolatedModules": true,
    "declaration": true,
    "sourceMap": true,
    "forceConsistentCasingInFileNames": true
  }
}
